								<div class="tier-deck-list">
									{tier.decks.map((deck) => (
										<img src={deck.art} alt={`${deck.name} icon`} title={deck.name} loading="lazy" />
									))}
								</div>
							</section>
						))}
					</div>
				</section>

				<section id="conclusion" class="article-block conclusion-block">
					<div class="section-header compact-header">
						<div>
							<h2>Conclusion</h2>
							<p>
								The new Starter Decks do not appear to create six brand-new dominant decks. What they do seem
								to do is redistribute key matchups across the field.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="conclusion-grid">
						<div class="conclusion-card">
							<h3>What changed most</h3>
							<p>
								Purple Katakuri currently looks like the most competitive of the six directly reinforced
								Leaders. ST31 Luffy, Kuzan, and Kid all seem capable of holding real meta share. Green Zoro
								still looks limited, while Sabo remains a high-variance development project.
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="conclusion-card">
							<h3>Who gained the most</h3>
							<p>
								The biggest winners may actually be Red/Green Luffy and Mihawk, both of which seem to convert
								the new red and green support into stronger, more coherent tournament plans than the face decks
								of the Starters themselves.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="closing-points">
						<p>Nami may lose ground if Mihawk and Red/Green Luffy both surge.</p>
						<p>Teach gains importance because of how cleanly it pressures Red/Green Luffy and Purple Enel.</p>
						<p>Purple Katakuri may benefit if Mihawk becomes one of the most played decks.</p>
						<p>Kuzan and Sabo still have substantial room to improve as lists get refined.</p>
					</div>

					<p class="final-note">
						OP16.5 should be a short format, but it may end up being noticeably more open than late OP16. The
						next wave of tournament results will tell us whether Red/Green Luffy and Mihawk really are the new
						decks to beat before OP17 arrives.
					</p>
				</section>
			</div>
		</div>
